Function Description <code>mh_audio_enumerate_playback_devices</code> Fill an array of <code>MH_AudioDeviceInfo</code> with available playback devices. Returns count <code>mh_audio_enumerate_capture_devices</code> Fill an array of <code>MH_AudioDeviceInfo</code> with available capture devices. Returns count <p><code>MH_AudioDeviceInfo</code> struct:</p> <ul> <li><code>char name[256]</code> -- device name (null-terminated)</li> <li><code>int is_default</code> -- <code>1</code> if this is the system default, else <code>0</code></li> </ul> <p>Typical usage:</p> <pre><code>MH_AudioDeviceInfo devices[32];
int count = mh_audio_enumerate_playback_devices(devices, 32);
for (int i = 0; i &lt; count; i++) {
    printf("[%d]%s %s\n", i, devices[i].is_default ? "*" : " ", devices[i].name);
}
</code></pre>
